  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Add the <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with<strong> boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7min until tender with a slight bite</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the&nbsp;<strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the&nbsp;<strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the white parts of the<strong> pak choi</strong>, keeping the green leaves whole</p>\r\n<p>Cut 2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> pieces of baking paper (or tin foil) approx. the size of A3 sheets of paper</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the sheets of baking paper to a large baking tray&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the white parts of the<strong> pak choi&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>(reserve the green leaves),<strong> fish sauce</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the baking paper</p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good old mix up&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Top with the&nbsp;<strong>mackerel fillets</strong>, skin-side up</p>\r\n<p>Season the <strong>mackerel fillets</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Scrunch the edges of the&nbsp;baking paper&nbsp;together around the <strong>pak&nbsp;choi</strong> and <strong>mackerel</strong>&nbsp;<strong>fillets</strong> to form a sealed parcel</p>\r\n<p>Put the baking tray in the oven for 15 min or until the mackerel&nbsp;is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Tip: your mackerel is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1347.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
